<!-- ROADMAP -->
<section id="roadmap">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header fade-in">
      <span class="section-label">Transparency</span>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>
      <h2>What We&rsquo;re Building Next</h2>
      <p>Three identified gaps. Three concrete plans. Honesty about where we are is itself a governance posture.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="roadmap-grid fade-in-group">
      <div class="roadmap-card">
        <span class="roadmap-timeline">Q2 2026</span>
        <h3>Formal Conflict Resolution Protocol</h3>
        <p>Programmatic merge-conflict handling when two agents write to the same resource simultaneously. <strong>Lock-acquire patterns</strong> prevent concurrent writes. <strong>Last-write-wins with full audit trail</strong> when locks aren&rsquo;t viable. Conflict log surfaced to the Primary for human review when stakes are high.</p>
        <div class="gap-reason"><span class="gap-reason-icon">&#8594;</span><span>Addresses Q4: simultaneous agent writes to shared resources currently resolved by routing architecture alone, not by code.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="roadmap-card">
        <span class="roadmap-timeline">Q2 2026</span>
        <h3>Authoritative Source Registry</h3>
        <p>Formal registry of canonical data sources per domain. Agents query the registry before using any data source. <strong>Unauthorized source usage is flagged automatically</strong> and routed to the relevant department manager. Registry itself is version-controlled and auditable.</p>
        <div class="gap-reason"><span class="gap-reason-icon">&#8594;</span><span>Addresses Q5: memory-first protocol is behavioral today; this makes source authority programmatic and enforceable.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="roadmap-card">
        <span class="roadmap-timeline">Q3 2026</span>
        <h3>Memory Staleness Detection</h3>
        <p>TTL on memory entries with configurable decay rates per domain. <strong>Confidence scores decay</strong> over time for volatile domains (market data, API specs). Automated re-verification triggers fire before stale memories influence decisions. Stale data quarantined, not deleted &mdash; full history preserved for audit.</p>
        <div class="gap-reason"><span class="gap-reason-icon">&#8594;</span><span>Addresses Q6: current staleness prevention is procedural (daily scans, handoffs); this makes it automatic and quantified.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA / FORM -->
